liveLayoutDetails.notes: On or over the parking lot or pavement is OB. Surrounded by water is OB. Discs must not enter restricted plane right of the marked tree. Go to drop zone with one penalty throw for all throws from the tee or drop zone that come to rest in the OB lake or miss the mandatory. Normal OB options including the drop zone for the rest of the hole. Rocks on shoreline are in bounds. Players may take 1-meter perpendicular relief from the rocks as if they were OB.

Surrounded by water is OB. On or over pavement/gravel road or outside of staked area is OB. Pier is OB. Rocks on the shoreline are in bounds. Players may take 1-meter perpendicular relief from the rocks as if they were OB.
On or over pavement to the left is OB. Beyond stakes right and long of basket is OB.
On or over path to the right is OB. Discs must not enter restricted plane right of the marked tree. If mandatory is missed, proceed to DZ with one penalty throw.

Ball field and outside of the staked area is OB. For throws from the tee area that come to rest OB, the next lie is restricted to either the drop zone or tee with a one throw penalty. Normal OB rules on the rest of the hole.
Outside of the staked area is OB.
Outside of the staked area is OB, on or over pavement to the right is OB.  Players may take 2m relief from creek.

Creek area marked by stakes in front of the tee is OB. Surrounded by water is OB. Over the creek to the left or right near the green is OB. On or over the road/staked line or parking lot to the right is OB. For discs that are OB, the optional drop zone may be used.

Outside of the staked area (including the bridge) is OB. For throws from the tee area that come to rest OB, the next lie is restricted to either the drop zone or tee with a one throw penalty. Normal OB rules on the rest of the hole.
Outside of the staked area is OB. Players may take 2m relief from creek.
Outside of the staked area is OB.

Outside of the staked area is OB. For throws from the tee area that come to rest OB, the next lie is restricted to either the drop zone or tee with a one throw penalty. Normal OB rules on the rest of the hole. Players may take free relief up to 30cm on a line perpendicular to the water tower base.

Surrounded by water is OB. Outside of the staked area (including the land by the tee) is OB. For throws from the tee area that come to rest OB, the next lie is restricted to either the drop zone or tee with a one throw penalty. Normal OB rules on the rest of the hole. Rocks on the shoreline are in bounds. Players may take 1-meter perpendicular relief from the rocks as if they were OB.

Surrounded by water is OB. Outside of the staked area is OB. On or across the bike path is OB. Rocks on the shoreline are in bounds. Players may take 1 m perpendicular relief from the rocks as if they were OB. For discs coming to rest within casual area marked with red paint, players may take free relief on the line of play, no closer to the target to the nearest point behind the painted area.

Outside of the staked area is OB. On/over bike path is OB. Discs must not enter restricted plane right of the marked pole. If mandatory is missed, proceed to DZ with one penalty throw. Players may take free relief up to 30cm on a line perpendicular to the cement base of the outhouse.
Outside of the staked area is OB. On or over road is OB. Discs must not enter restricted plane right of the marked pole. If mandatory is missed, proceed to DZ with one penalty throw.

Surrounded by lake and outside of the staked area is OB. Stakes inside hay bales marks OB by lake. Pier is OB. For throws from the tee area that come to rest OB, the next lie is restricted to either drop zone A or tee with a one throw penalty. Normal OB on the rest of the hole.

Surrounded by lake is OB. On or over pavement or outside of staked area is OB. Handicap platform area is OB. Discs must not enter restricted space right of the marked tree. Rethrow from the previous lie without a penalty throw for missing the mandatory (still counting the throw that missed the mandatory). For discs coming to rest within casual areas marked with red paint, players may take free relief on the line of play, no closer to the target to the nearest point behind the painted area.
Woods on left are OB where marked. Lake is OB. Fence and beyond on right side of fairway is OB; inside edge of the fence posts define the OB line. Golf Greens and Tee Boxes are OB.
On/Over cart paths OB. Golf Greens and Tee Boxes OB.
On/over the cart path to the right is OB. Golf green OB. Sand traps play as hazards.

Golf green OB. Water/Pond is OB. On/over cart path is OB.**Private property on left side of fairway OB where marked by stakes. **OB Green - WARNING: Green is OB. Please DO NOT walk on greens.  Sand traps play as hazards.
Water OB. Golf Greens and Tee Boxes OB. Sand traps play as hazard.

Cart path on right is OB line until where marked at end of tree line, then turns right, and connects to the 2nd cart path which becomes OB line from there. Pond is OB. Golf Greens and Tee Boxes are OB. Left side of fairway and where marked OB. Sand traps are hazard.
On or over golf fairways on left and right are OB as marked. Golf Green is OB. Off course property to the left is OB. Sand traps are hazard.
Golf greens are OB. Marked line shared with hole 9 and beyond is OB. Sand traps are hazard.
Pond is OB. Golf tee box is OB. On/over cart paths where marked is OB. Over the far-right side of the golf fairway is OB where marked.
Private backyards behind basket are OB (white columns mark OB line). Area left where marked is OB. On/Over Cart Path is OB. Marked area around barn is OB; Players may take up to 1M relief from barn.
Water is OB. Golf green is OB. Residential area long of hole is OB. Sand taps are hazard. Note: Do not go onto private property.
Surrounded by water is OB. Right side where marked is OB. Practice Greens OB. Parking Lot OB. Golf Tee Box OB. White rock area OB. Cart Paths are in bounds on this hole.

Island Green. Tall Grass where marked is OB. Cart Path leading to Green is OB where marked. If Tee shot goes OB, next lie is restricted to Drop Zone or previous lie with one penalty throw. Standard OB rules apply on all subsequent throws.
In/Over tall grass on both sides of the fairway is OB. Fence and beyond is OB; inside edge of the fence posts define the OB line.
Left side as marked all the way behind the basket is OB.  Fence line and private property on right side of fairway is OB.
Practice greens are OB. Tall Grass on left OB where marked.

Tall grass on the left side is OB. Marked area on right side of tee is OB. Mandatory tree about 305 ft. from the tee. Discs must not enter restricted plane right of the marked tree. If mandatory is missed, proceed to DZ with one penalty throw.
Patio area and practice greens are OB.
